Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.23,0:01:22.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,历史频道 - 宇宙 第4季第10集 脉冲星和类星体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The History Channel - The Universe s04e10 Pulsar & Quasars
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.45,0:01:29.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,1967年 地球上的科学家取得了一项惊人的发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In 1967, scientists on planet Earth made a startling discovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.58,0:01:34.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有东西 有人 正通过太空向我们发送信号\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Something, someone, was sending us signals through space.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.80,0:01:37.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,莫非是外星人在向我们发送信息么？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Were aliens trying to send us a message?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.43,0:01:41.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,脉冲星首次发现时 让我们大吃一惊\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When pulsars were first discovered, they blew us away.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.35,0:01:44.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,夜空中有东西在不停地打开关闭\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Something in the night sky was turning on and off.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.94,0:01:48.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,自然界怎么会有东西在干那事的呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How could something in nature do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.02,0:01:51.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因而我们就把它们叫做继电器对象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And so we actually called them LGM objects.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.61,0:01:53.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那代表了小绿人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That stood for little green men.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.44,0:01:56.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,英国天文学家检测到了信号\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Astronomers in England detected the signals
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.03,0:01:59.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,利用的是早期的射电望远镜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}using a primitive radio telescope,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.82,0:02:05.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个庞大的电线和电杆的列阵 占据了四英亩多的土地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a massive array of poles and wires stretched out over four acres of land.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.00,0:02:07.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,首批信号\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The first of the signals
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.29,0:02:10.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并不只是孤立的无线电噪音的波峰\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was not just an isolated peak in the radio noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.83,0:02:16.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是有规律的脉冲 每1.3秒精准地重复一次\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was a regular blip, precisely repeating every 1.3 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.76,0:02:20.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而 在当年 科学家就意识到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Within a year, though, scientists realized
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.64,0:02:23.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有规律的信号背后并无外星人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}aliens were not behind the regular signals.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.30,0:02:27.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,相反 它们出自快速旋转的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Instead, they came from rapidly rotating stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.68,0:02:31.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,“脉冲星”成了新现象抢眼的名字\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}"Pulsar" became the catchy name for the new phenomenon,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.31,0:02:33.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是脉动恒星的简称\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}short for pulsating star.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.53,0:02:38.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,脉冲星看上去在不停地眨眼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A pulsar seems to blink on and off
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.03,0:02:44.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为旋转的恒星正从其磁场中发出能量束\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because the rotating star is sending out beams of energy from its magnetic field,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.16,0:02:47.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并没有与其旋转轴保持一致\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is not aligned with its axis of rotation.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.50,0:02:52.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当其经过我们的视野时 我们看到闪光般的光束\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We see the beam as a flash of light when it passes across our field of view.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.46,0:02:59.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,脉冲星发出的光束原理很大程度就像这个警灯\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The beam coming out of a pulsar works a lot like this emergency beacon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.17,0:03:00.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在来看看它是如何闪烁的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now take a look at how it flashes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.72,0:03:02.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它不仅在不停地闪烁\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's not just blinking on and off.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.47,0:03:04.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在外罩里 警灯有一个旋转的反射镜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Inside the housing, the beacon has a rotating reflector
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.97,0:03:08.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,把光线360度地扫射\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that sweeps the light around 360 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.22,0:03:09.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只要我们有光束的基准线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As long as we have line of sight with the beam,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.93,0:03:12.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它每次转动都会掠过我们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it sweeps by us every time it goes around.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.10,0:03:14.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过它看上去就是断断续续的闪烁\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But it looks like it's flashing on and off.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.40,0:03:20.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,旋转的脉冲星看来不停闪烁是同样的道理\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A rotating pulsar looks like it is flashing on and off for the same reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.16,0:03:30.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而脉冲星并不只是随便那种旋转的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But a pulsar isn't just any kind of rotating star.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.29,0:03:32.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它是旋转的中子星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a rotating neutron star,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.87,0:03:38.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一种怪异的物体 诞生于大质量恒星以超新星结束生命之时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an exotic object created when a big, massive star ends its life in a supernova.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.68,0:03:49.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,天体物理学家帕特.斯莱恩用一个迷人的方法向我们演示\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Astrophysicist Pat Slane has a fascinating way to show us
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.39,0:03:52.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,超新星爆发后留下的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what's left over after the supernova,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.94,0:03:55.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,恒星残核的压力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when the pressure of the star's remaining core
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.10,0:03:58.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,已不再能够抵抗重力了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}can no longer fight against the force of gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.24,0:04:01.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我在这里要演示的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What I'm going to demonstrate here
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.65,0:04:06.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是我们从这个55加仑的罐子里抽去空气后的情景\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is what happens when we remove the air from the interior of this 55-gallon drum
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.91,0:04:10.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,让地球的大气 空气的重量来压垮它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and let the atmosphere of the Earth, the weight of the air, crush it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.25,0:04:15.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这类似于大质量恒星内部在其晚年所发生的情景\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is similar to what happens at the interior of a massive star late in its life.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.63,0:04:17.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在其失去压力支撑后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When it loses its pressure support,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.38,0:04:19.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,恒星开始垮塌 就有了一个超新星爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the star collapses, and there's a supernova explosion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.27,0:04:35.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,垮塌后的恒星残骸变成了中子星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The crushed stellar remnant becomes the neutron star
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.94,0:04:38.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,质量是我们太阳的1.4倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with a mass 1.4 times our Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.98,0:04:42.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,缩小到了曼哈顿大小的球体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}reduced to a sphere the size of Manhattan.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.15,0:04:45.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它是世上最离奇的物体之一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It is one of the most bizarre objects in nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.41,0:04:49.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你必须明白中子星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You have to understand that a neutron star
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.08,0:04:53.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是在垮塌成黑洞之前勉强支撑的物体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is matter barely holding up before it collapses into a black hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.12,0:04:54.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其引力强大到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The gravity is so strong
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.91,0:04:58.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将电子压进了原子核\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that it has crushed electrons into the nucleus of an atom
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.08,0:04:59.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从而变成了中子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and made neutrons.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.13,0:05:00.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,令人拍案\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.46,0:05:05.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你有方糖那样的东西 举个例子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you take something like a sugar cube, for example,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.63,0:05:07.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,约一立方厘米\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about a cubic centimeter.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.64,0:05:10.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果这方糖是由中子星材料构成的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If this sugar cube were made of neutron star material,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.01,0:05:13.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它就会有近十亿吨重\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it would weigh close to a billion tons.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.89,0:05:17.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,想想8000艘航母的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Think of it as something like 8,000 aircraft carriers
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.48,0:05:21.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在那么大的 密度大得难以置信的物体里头\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in something that size, incredibly dense objects.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.11,0:05:28.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,新诞生的中子星会不由自主地产生高速旋转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The newly created neutron star can't help having a high-speed spin.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.66,0:05:31.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所有的恒星 我们知道都在旋转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All stars that we know about are already rotating,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.99,0:05:34.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此当大质量恒星压缩成中子星后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so when a massive star compresses into a neutron star,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.00,0:05:37.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,旋转同样被压缩了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the rotation is compressed also.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.25,0:05:38.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就像是滑冰者\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's just like an ice skater.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.75,0:05:41.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当滑冰者旋转收拢她的双臂\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When an ice skater spins and she pulls her arms in,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.00,0:05:43.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就会旋转加快\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}she spins faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.34,0:05:51.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,飞旋的中子星是一个巨大的天然发电机\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The spinning neutron star is a massive natural electric generator.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.10,0:05:54.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其旋转会产生强大的磁场\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Its spin creates a powerful magnetic field.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.43,0:05:58.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,磁力会攫取电子和其它原子粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The magnetic force grabs onto electrons and other atomic particles
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.81,0:06:02.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并以高速将它们抛入太空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and flings them into space at high speeds.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.15,0:06:04.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,高速粒子无一例外地会喷射辐射\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}High-speed particles always emit radiation,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.98,0:06:08.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在中子星上 它们会成束喷出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and in pulsars, they're coming out in beams.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.15,0:06:11.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些就是我们所看到的脉冲 但我们所见到的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These are the pulses we see, but we see them
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.70,0:06:14.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只有当这些波束对准我们这方向时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}only when the beams are pointed in our direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.41,0:06:17.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,已知有多少中子星？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How many pulsars are known?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.29,0:06:20.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,约超过1800颗 这数字还在快速增长\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's something over 1,800, and the number is growing rapidly,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.38,0:06:24.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为我们一直都有新的中子星的不断发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because we continue to discover new pulsars all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.13,0:06:26.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而现存的中子星数目 -\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the number of pulsars that exist--
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.88,0:06:29.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些全都是在我们的星系 银河系里发现的 -\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and these are all found in our galaxy, the Milky Way--
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.68,0:06:32.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要远大于那个数目\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Is many, many times larger than that,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.68,0:06:37.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为波束 是以电波为主的 是极小的部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because the beams, that are seen in radio primarily, are very small,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.39,0:06:41.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此我们只看到了所有存在的中子星的极小一部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and so we only see a tiny fraction of all the pulsars that are out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.40,0:06:47.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过每个中子星都有完全不同的旋转速度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But each pulsar has a completely different rotational speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.57,0:06:52.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最慢的每9.437秒旋转一圈\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The slowest rotates once every 9.437 seconds,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.37,0:06:57.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而最快的每秒旋转716圈\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the fastest goes around 716 times every second.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.37,0:06:59.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果我们立足其表面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If we stood on its surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.08,0:07:03.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们会每小时跑上9700多万英里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we'd be going more than 97 million miles per hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.08,0:07:06.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那将比我们在地球上的旅行快上1000万倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's about 10 million times faster than we travel on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.38,0:07:12.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每颗中子星都有独一无二的旋转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Every pulsar has an absolutely unique spin.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.76,0:07:14.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其旋转有特定的速率\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It goes around at a given rate,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.76,0:07:18.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就像是人的指纹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that's just like a fingerprint for an individual.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.60,0:07:22.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以如果你知道了其特有的旋转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So if you know what that characteristic spin is,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.06,0:07:24.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你就知道是哪颗脉冲星了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}then you know what that pulsar is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.57,0:07:28.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由于所有的脉冲星都有自己的签名\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Since all pulsars have their own signatures,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.53,0:07:32.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你就可以利用它们来确定你在太空中的位置\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you can use them as tools to determine your location in space,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.86,0:07:35.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个想法已被航天局所利用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an idea that has been used by NASA.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.41,0:07:41.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们送入外太阳系的一些航天器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some of the spacecraft we've sent into the outer parts of the solar system,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.25,0:07:46.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如先锋号和旅行者号 都带有太空地图\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like Pioneer and Voyager, have had maps of space which 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.25,0:07:53.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,标明了我们太阳系相对于若干脉冲星位置的定位\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}show our solar system's location relative to the locations of a bunch of pulsars.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.97,0:08:02.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太空中的脉冲星可以用来定位地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The pulsars in space can be used to locate the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.94,0:08:06.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,无异于我们的GPS设备利用多个卫星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the same way that our GPS devices use multiple satellites
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.94,0:08:09.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来定位地面上的位置\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to locate a position on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.36,0:08:12.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,希望有朝一日\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's hoped one day
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.11,0:08:15.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,另一族太空旅行者能发现其中的一个航天器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}another race of space travelers will find one of the spacecraft
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.66,0:08:18.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,读取地图来获悉它来自何处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and read the map to learn where it came from.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.54,0:08:23.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,足够聪明的外星人能够搞明白我们在哪里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A sufficiently intelligent alien could figure out where we are
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.87,0:08:26.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,通过测量所有这些同样的脉冲星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by measuring all these same pulsars
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.46,0:08:29.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,计算出我们相对它们的位置\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and figuring out where we are in relation to them,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.00,0:08:32.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为每颗脉冲星都有一个独特的周期\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because each pulsar has a unique period.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.01,0:08:35.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每颗脉冲星的独特旋转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The unique spin of each pulsar
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.97,0:08:39.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也让它们成为了超精确的天文钟\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}also makes them super-accurate astronomical clocks,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.76,0:08:43.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,走时优于地球上最好的原子钟\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}keeping better time than the best atomic clocks here on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.81,0:08:47.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,脉冲星之所以精准是因为它们是天然的终极飞轮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Pulsars are so accurate because they're nature's ultimate flywheel.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.02,0:08:50.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是一个普通的自行车轮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is an ordinary bicycle tire mounted on a repair rack
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.57,0:08:51.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,装在这自行车店里的修理架上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}here in this bicycle shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.03,0:08:54.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个轮子非常像脉冲星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And this wheel is very much like a pulsar.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.15,0:08:55.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来把它转起来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Let's give it a spin.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.82,0:08:58.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你看到轮子旋转平稳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So you see the wheel is rotating very smoothly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.53,0:08:59.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有一点点慢下来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's very little to slow it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.03,0:09:03.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好 对于太空中的脉冲星来说 几乎没什么让它慢下来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, for a pulsar in space, there's almost nothing to slow it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.08,0:09:06.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,请注意轮子的旋转约每秒两圈\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now notice that the wheel is rotating about a couple times a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.17,0:09:09.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是普通脉冲星的平均转速\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's the average speed of rotation for an average pulsar.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.54,0:09:12.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当然 这轮子只有几英尺的直径\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, of course, this wheel is only a few feet across,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.88,0:09:15.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而真正的脉冲星以同样速度旋转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}whereas a real pulsar is spinning at the same speed,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.68,0:09:17.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会有曼哈顿那般大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but it's the size of Manhattan.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.39,0:09:21.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过没什么是永恒不变的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But nothing is forever,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.76,0:09:24.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即使是脉冲星也会随着时间而减慢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and even pulsars slow down over time,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.73,0:09:27.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尽管是非常地缓慢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}although they do it very slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.35,0:09:31.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,阐述脉冲星旋转的同一个轮子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The same bicycle wheel that illustrates the pulsar's spin
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.11,0:09:34.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还演示了其速度放慢的原因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}also demonstrates what makes it slow down.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.82,0:09:40.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,脉冲星把旋转能转变成辐射\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Pulsars convert rotational energy into radiation,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.16,0:09:42.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在此过程中 它们就不得不放慢速度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and in the process, they have to slow down.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.24,0:09:43.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来看看它是如何作用于这个车轮的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Let's see how it works with the bicycle wheel.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.04,0:09:46.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在轮子转动很快\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, the wheel is moving pretty quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.04,0:09:47.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果我把手放到边缘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If I put my hand to the rim,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.67,0:09:50.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我可以在我的指尖上将转动能转变成热能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I can convert rotational energy to heat energy in my fingers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.54,0:09:51.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好痛\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ouch.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.63,0:09:53.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在车轮慢了下来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now the wheel has slowed down.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.88,0:09:57.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在真正的脉冲星上 比起我的手更像是羽毛轻拂\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In a real pulsar, it would be more like the action of a feather than my hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.68,0:10:00.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为脉冲星的能量丧失非常缓慢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because pulsars lose energy very, very slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.43,0:10:05.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,脉冲星 每秒旋转一次\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A pulsar, spinning once every second,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.27,0:10:10.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有可能百万年里只放慢百分之三秒\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}may slow down by about only three hundreths of a second in a million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.23,0:10:16.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过 偶尔 脉冲星确实会稍有加速\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Occasionally, though, a pulsar may actually speed up slightly
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.90,0:10:20.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种现象与中子星的星壳有关\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in a phenomenon linked to a neutron star's crust,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.32,0:10:24.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一层比钢铁坚固100亿倍的物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a layer of matter 10 billion times stronger than steel,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.62,0:10:27.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但受制于“星震”\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and yet subject to "starquakes."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.00,0:10:33.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,中子星并非通体都是固体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Neutron stars are not solids all the way through.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.63,0:10:34.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们有一个星壳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They have a crust.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.00,0:10:37.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,星壳异常坚固\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that crust is incredibly strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.80,0:10:39.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是中子星里还是有力道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But there are forces within the neutron star
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.84,0:10:42.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有可能偶尔会使星壳产生裂缝\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that can occasionally cause the crust to crack.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.72,0:10:48.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一旦产生裂缝 整个中子星会重新调整自己\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When it cracks, the whole neutron star readjusts itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.31,0:10:52.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,中子星的旋转会产生变化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it produces a change in the rotation of the neutron star.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.36,0:10:53.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们称其为脉冲星的自转突变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We call it a glitch.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.44,0:10:54.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,星壳破裂\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The crust is cracked.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.90,0:10:57.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,中子星上就会产生星震\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There has been a starquake on this neutron star.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.95,0:11:01.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尽管脉冲星的奇异世界里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Though the strange world of pulsars
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.99,0:11:05.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,包括了诸如自转突变和星震之类的有趣事件\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}includes intriguing events like glitches and starquakes,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.74,0:11:08.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但你还是很难在望远镜捕获到它们时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you'd hardly know it from the tiny blinks seen
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.16,0:11:10.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从所看到的细微的闪烁中了解它们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when they're captured by telescopes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.87,0:11:12.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过脉冲星在把致命的辐射\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But what happens when pulsars
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.83,0:11:15.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,抛入宇宙云里时会发生什么情况呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are hurling deadly radiation into cosmic clouds
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.00,0:11:19.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,先前其母星随着太空中的巨大爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}after their parent stars have ripped holes in the galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.55,0:11:21.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,已经在星系中撕开了大口\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with their massive explosions in space?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.39,0:11:28.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,又会对挡道的芸芸众生有何影响呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What will their impact be on any living beings in their path?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.90,0:11:40.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,超新星的致命爆发无限精彩\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The deadly explosions of supernovas are endlessly fascinating.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.53,0:11:44.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们是暮年恒星的咆哮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They are the violent screams of aging stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.45,0:11:46.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,怒其渐渐老去\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}outraged at having to grow old.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.92,0:11:57.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,强烈的爆发不只是杀死挡道的芸芸众生\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The powerful blasts would do more than kill any living beings in their path.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.71,0:12:04.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,超新星会抹去围绕着爆发恒星的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A supernova would wipe out all traces of any civilization
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.09,0:12:06.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,行星上的所有文明的痕迹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on a planet in orbit around the exploding star.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.14,0:12:14.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,星系里充满了这些爆发留下的色彩斑斓的余波\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The galaxy is full of the colorful aftereffects of these explosions.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.56,0:12:19.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们是巨大的星际残骸云 称为超新星遗迹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They are gigantic clouds of stellar debris called supernova remnants.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.03,0:12:24.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你要是想搜寻脉冲星 那里是最佳之处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And if you're searching for a pulsar, that's the best place to look.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.07,0:12:29.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,脉冲星确实可以在超新星遗迹找到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Pulsars are actually found in supernova remnants.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.41,0:12:32.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是因为脉冲星形成于超新星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's because pulsars are formed in a supernova,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.25,0:12:33.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,爆发的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an exploding star.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.67,0:12:38.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,虽然有些脉冲星加速远离\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}While some pulsars speed away from
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.96,0:12:41.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或另立门户于它们的超新星遗迹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or simply outlive their supernova remnants,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.92,0:12:45.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但其它则还是旋转在遗迹之中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}others remain spinning inside them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.05,0:12:47.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在那里 它们照亮了周围的壳体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There, they light up the surrounding shell
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.93,0:12:51.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,创造出所谓的脉冲星风星云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and create what's called a pulsar wind nebula.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.14,0:12:58.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,脉冲星产生的风完全不是我们在地球上所认为的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The wind from a pulsar is not quite like what we think of on Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.19,0:12:59.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是空气流动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is air blowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.77,0:13:03.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个风却是由粒子和辐射组成的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Instead it's a wind made of particles and radiation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.28,0:13:07.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是风速极高\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But it's blowing out at very high speeds,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.95,0:13:10.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大大快于我们在地球上的任何东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}much faster than anything we have here on Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.45,0:13:12.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,速度高到携带大量的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}high enough that it carries a lot of energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.75,0:13:15.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能量与爆发恒星的残留的物质相互作用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the energy interacts with the material
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.66,0:13:20.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使之点亮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that's left over from the exploding star to cause it to light up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.25,0:13:22.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,迄今为止 脉冲星风星云中最壮观的例子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By far, the most spectacular example
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.63,0:13:26.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们所知的就是蟹状星云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of a pulsar wind nebula that we know about is the Crab Nebula,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.05,0:13:28.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它有一颗旋转的中子星在其中央\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which has a spinning neutron star at its center,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.30,0:13:30.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就是它让整体熠熠生辉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that's what energizes the whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.14,0:13:37.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,蟹状星云是著名的超新星遗迹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Crab Nebula is a famous supernova remnant
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.94,0:13:41.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,出自公元1054年出现的超新星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from the supernova that occurred in the year 1054 A.D.,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.65,0:13:43.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,亚洲天文学家有过研究\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}studied by Asian astronomers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.45,0:13:48.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,超新星本身可见于天上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The supernova itself could be seen in the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.86,0:13:51.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,历时数周直至逐渐消失\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for weeks before fading away,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.37,0:13:54.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没想到近700年后被重新发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}only to be rediscovered nearly 700 years later
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.83,0:13:59.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,成为了超新星遗迹 观察只能通过望远镜了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as a supernova remnant, visible only through telescopes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.79,0:14:05.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,蟹状星云中的脉冲星发现于1968年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The pulsar in the Crab Nebula was discovered in 1968,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.13,0:14:07.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,首颗脉冲星发现后不久\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}very soon after the first pulsar.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.93,0:14:12.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它证实了脉冲星出自超新星的说法\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it confirmed the theory that pulsars came from supernovas.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.06,0:14:17.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从地球上看 蟹状星云中的脉冲星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Seen from the Earth, the pulsar in the Crab Nebula
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.52,0:14:19.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,貌似一个微不足道的小不点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}looks like an insignificant speck.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.98,0:14:25.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在其被确定为脉冲星之前 没有人意识到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Before it was identified as a pulsar, no one realized
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.69,0:14:29.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它居然是每秒闪烁30次\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it was actually blinking on and off 30 times a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.82,0:14:32.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在一张典型的长曝光的望远镜照片里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In a typical long-exposure photo from a telescope,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.99,0:14:35.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它只是表现为普通的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it registers simply as an ordinary star.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.54,0:14:39.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每秒30次太快了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Well, 30 times a second is too fast
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.87,0:14:42.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,谁都没法看清蟹状星云的闪烁\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for anyone to actually see the Crab Pulsar blinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.67,0:14:46.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,取而代之的是 我们必须用上一种高速摄影技术\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Instead, we have to use a kind of high-speed photographic technique
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.21,0:14:48.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,叫做光子计数器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}called a photon counter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.05,0:14:50.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它能够拍摄飞快 足以\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's able to take pictures fast enough
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.05,0:14:52.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,看清脉冲星的闪烁\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to actually see the pulsar blinking on and off.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.76,0:14:53.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它会呈现出 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It appears to be on
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.97,0:14:56.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,打开时脉冲星光束转向我们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when the pulsar beam rotates toward us,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.06,0:14:58.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,关闭时光束转离了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it's off when the beam rotates away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.65,0:15:07.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,难以置信的是脉冲星的威力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What's incredible is the power of the pulsar.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.11,0:15:10.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们看到蟹状星云里的一切都栩栩生辉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Everything we see in the Crab Nebula is glowing
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.32,0:15:14.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,源于那颗旋转的中子星源源不断的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because of the energy streaming out of that single spinning neutron star.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.75,0:15:20.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,蟹状星云中央的中子星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The neutron star in the middle of the Crab Nebula
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.16,0:15:22.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,直径也许就10英里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has a diameter of perhaps 10 miles,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.79,0:15:27.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但却照亮了周围数光年的气体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but it's lighting up the gas around it for several light-years.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.05,0:15:29.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个小不点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So this eensy-beensy thing
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.13,0:15:32.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,点亮了周围一个巨大的区域\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is lighting up a tremendously large region around it
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.43,0:15:35.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为所有的高能带电粒子都出自它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because of all the energetic charged particles coming away from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.60,0:15:39.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,脉冲星点亮的超新星遗迹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The pulsar is lighting up a supernova remnant
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.43,0:15:41.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,直径6光年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}six light-years in diameter,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.64,0:15:46.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,相当于近38万个天文单位\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}equivalent to nearly 380,000 astronomical units.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.61,0:15:49.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个天文单位 简称AU\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}An astronomical unit, or an AU,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.49,0:15:53.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,通常用来描述宇宙中的距离\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Is commonly used to describe distance in the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.07,0:15:55.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科罗拉多州丹佛市威尔\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Will W. of Denver, Colorado,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.41,0:16:00.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,询问《宇宙》节目：天文单位是啥东西？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}wants to ask "The Universe" just what an AU is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.25,0:16:02.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,威尔 了解一下有好处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Will, that's a useful thing to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.46,0:16:05.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我一下子的回答就是天文单位\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}My snappy answer is that an astronomical unit
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.50,0:16:07.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有点搞脑筋的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is one heck of a big apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.38,0:16:09.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过 言归正传 天文单位\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But, really, the astronomical unit
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.13,0:16:12.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就是地球与太阳之间的平均距离\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is the average distance between the Earth and the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.30,0:16:17.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那约是9300万英里 或等于1.5亿公里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, that's about 93 million miles, or, equivalently, 150 million kilometers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.27,0:16:27.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,蟹状星云深处的混沌\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The chaos deep inside the Crab Nebula is revealed by time-lapse pictures
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.27,0:16:30.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在X射线和可见光下的延时摄像中暴露无遗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in both X-rays and visible light.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.32,0:16:35.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,旋转恒星的脉冲星风在其赤道周围产生了冲击波\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The spinning star's pulsar wind creates shock waves around its equator,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.11,0:16:39.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,此时两极不停地喷出汹涌的喷射\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}while polar jets are shooting out in turbulent streams.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.49,0:16:43.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此这是个非常具有活力的星系  令人激动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So this is a very dynamic system, an exciting one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.71,0:16:46.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,天文学中 人人都在研究蟹状星云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And everybody in astronomy studies the Crab Nebula.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.17,0:16:49.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,与大多数脉冲星一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Like most pulsars,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.67,0:16:54.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,蟹状星云里的那个也在逐渐放缓\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the one inside the Crab Nebula is gradually slowing down,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.17,0:16:59.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但约有10%的脉冲星被发现有一个大规模的加速过程\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but about 10% of all pulsars have found a method of speeding up in a big way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.81,0:17:03.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们被称为毫秒脉冲星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're called millisecond pulsars.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.35,0:17:08.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,毫秒脉冲星就是我们所谓的再生脉冲星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Millisecond pulsars are what we call recycled pulsars.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.31,0:17:09.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们曾经是普通的脉冲星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They used to be ordinary pulsars.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.02,0:17:11.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们停止了脉冲\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They stopped pulsing,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.15,0:17:13.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随后因为它们处在一个双星系里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and then because they were in a binary system,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.03,0:17:16.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也就是说 附近有一颗恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that is, there was another star nearby
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.20,0:17:19.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们会从中窃取一些物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that they could steal some mass from,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.41,0:17:20.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从而旋转起来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they're spun up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.87,0:17:24.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因而它们就加速到毫秒级速度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So their speed increases to millisecond speeds.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.21,0:17:31.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每当有东西落入脉冲星时 它就会得到一次刺激\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Each time something falls onto the pulsar, it gets a kick,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.34,0:17:34.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为来自同伴的星际物质旋入了其中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because the stellar matter from the companion swirls onto it,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.01,0:17:37.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而不是直接落在其表面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}instead of dropping straight to the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.05,0:17:39.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,旋转的自行车轮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The rotating bicycle wheel
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.26,0:17:42.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,表明了脉冲星的加速过程\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}illustrates how the process makes the pulsar speed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.52,0:17:44.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,车轮在旋转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The wheel is spinning,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.89,0:17:47.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我的手就像是来自伴星的物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and my hand is like the matter from the companion star.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.81,0:17:49.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为它具有旋转的势头\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Because it has rotational momentum,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.65,0:17:52.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它转向里面 如这样打击恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it swirls inward and strikes the star like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.61,0:17:54.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,增加了它的转速\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}increasing its speed of rotation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.57,0:17:57.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并不像这样突然刹车\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It doesn't drop down like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.24,0:18:03.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实际上 毫秒脉冲星获得的速度是相当惊人的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In nature, the speeds attained by millisecond pulsars are breathtaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.91,0:18:07.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,脉冲星每秒旋转数百圈\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Pulsars spin several hundred times a second,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.62,0:18:10.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,甚至最快的会高达每秒上千圈\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}even up to maybe a thousand times a second for the fastest ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.67,0:18:11.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那可非同寻常\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's very unusual,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.96,0:18:15.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为你想想曼哈顿那般大小的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because you're talking about something the size of maybe Manhattan,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.17,0:18:17.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每秒钟旋转数百圈\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}spinning a few hundred times a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.51,0:18:19.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它会让你眼花缭乱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That would make you pretty dizzy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.59,0:18:22.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还有比毫秒脉冲星更为奇特的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even more exotic than millisecond pulsars
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.26,0:18:26.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,怪兽 叫做磁星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are the strange beasts known as magnetars.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.77,0:18:29.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,磁星极为罕见\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Magnetars are extremely rare.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.23,0:18:32.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,事实上 我们在1979年之前对其一无所知\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In fact, we didn't even know about any of them until 1979.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.98,0:18:35.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,甚至在当时 我们都不确定我们看到了什么\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And even then, we weren't sure exactly what we were looking at.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.44,0:18:40.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在我们知道在我们星系4000亿颗恒星里头\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now we know of only about 15 magnetars
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.11,0:18:43.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只有约15颗磁星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}amongst the 400 billion stars in our galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.79,0:18:48.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,脉冲星 已知一开始就具有很强的磁场\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Pulsars are known to have strong magnetic fields to begin with,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.21,0:18:52.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但磁星将磁性推向了极致\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but magnetars take magnetism to the extreme.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.21,0:18:56.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,磁星的磁场极其强烈\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The magnetic field of a magnetar is intense.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.71,0:19:02.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它是地球磁场强度的上千万亿倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a thousand million million times the magnetic field strength of the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.09,0:19:05.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在 要是附近有一颗磁星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, if there were a magnetar anywhere nearby,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.31,0:19:08.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就会抹去全世界所有的信用卡的磁性\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it would de-magnetize all the credit cards in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.44,0:19:13.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过信用卡对人类已无太大的用处了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But credit cards wouldn't be of much use to humans
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.65,0:19:17.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们每一个分子都已被磁星给拆开了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}whose very molecules may be pulled apart by a magnetar.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.82,0:19:23.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,磁星具有整个宇宙间最强的磁场\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Magnetars have the strongest magnetic field in the whole universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.53,0:19:26.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不清楚人类究竟能否生存在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's unclear exactly if humans could even live
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.49,0:19:28.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那样强的磁场之中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}amongst a magnetic field that strong,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.12,0:19:31.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为磁性会将水分子拆开\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because the magnetism tends to pull water molecules apart
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.96,0:19:33.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,变成拉长的结构\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into elongated structures.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.83,0:19:36.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,难料人类是否还能存活\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's doubtful that people could even live.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.76,0:19:45.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,仿佛磁星和毫秒脉冲星还不够怪异\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And as if magnetars and millisecond pulsars weren't bizarre enough,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.10,0:19:47.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在银河系的星系插曲中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the Milky Way's galactic sideshow,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.64,0:19:50.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还有其它怪胎 更令人瞠目结舌\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there are other freaks, even more mind-blowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.31,0:19:55.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有机会发现孪生脉冲星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What are the chances of finding twin pulsars,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.90,0:19:57.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,带有行星的脉冲星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}pulsars with planets,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.77,0:20:01.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以及与《感恩而死》的鼓手合作的脉冲星吗？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and pulsars joining the drummer of The Grateful Dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.37,0:20:08.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,去掉节拍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Take the click off.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.54,0:20:11.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来见见米奇.哈特 一位长期鼓手\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Meet Mickey Hart, longtime drummer,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.12,0:20:14.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他的成名作是《感恩而死》\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}who first gained fame with The Grateful Dead,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.63,0:20:18.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在在制作太空中的脉冲星节拍的音乐\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and now makes music to the beat of pulsars from space.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.88,0:20:23.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我想与宇宙组织互动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I wanted to interact with the fabric of the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.84,0:20:27.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,把我们打击进创世的东西 种子声音\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the things that blew us into creation, the seed sounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.18,0:20:33.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些电磁波 我们已经将其转换成了声波\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So these electromagnetic waves we've transferred into sonic waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.35,0:20:35.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,脉冲星特别有趣\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Pulsars are especially interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.36,0:20:42.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,脉冲星发出的那些电磁波\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Those electromagnetic waves from pulsars
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.15,0:20:45.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,传给我们的最明显的就是电波的形式\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}reach us most clearly in the form of radio waves,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.36,0:20:47.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,划过苍穹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}sweeping across the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.20,0:20:50.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,奇异的波束使脉冲星脱颖而出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the freakish beams that make pulsars stand out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.87,0:20:55.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,脉冲星产生大量的电波\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Pulsars produce a lot of radio waves,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.00,0:20:58.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,完全不同于普通的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that's quite unlike normal stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.67,0:21:02.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,普通恒星的光芒几乎都是可见光波\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Normal stars shine mostly at visible optical wavelengths.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.05,0:21:05.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此你一旦看到有明亮的射电源出现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So when you see a bright radio source out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.43,0:21:06.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就会引起你的注意\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it captures your attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.97,0:21:09.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,另外要是有哔哔哔的声音\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And if in addition, it's going beep beep beep,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.47,0:21:11.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就真的抓住你的眼球了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}then it really captures your attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.93,0:21:14.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们还非常幸运 电波可以\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're also very lucky that radio waves can
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.52,0:21:16.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,让自己经过我们星系的漫长距离\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}make it through long distances in our galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.77,0:21:19.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不受气体尘埃的干扰\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}without being affected by the intervening gas and dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.23,0:21:21.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们还让自己经过我们的大气层\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And they make it through our own atmosphere as well
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.86,0:21:23.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而没有任何干扰\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}without any trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.86,0:21:27.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过也许关于脉冲星电波束最令人兴奋的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But perhaps what's most exciting about pulsar radio beams
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.61,0:21:31.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就是它们来自数百光年以外\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is that they come from hundreds of light-years away.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.49,0:21:35.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过要将它们输入耳机或扬声器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But pipe them into a set of headphones or speakers,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.29,0:21:37.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们才能真正听到它们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we can actually listen to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.83,0:21:42.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对于较慢的 你所听到的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For slow ones, what you hear
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.13,0:21:47.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就是每一圈一次的扬声器的撞击\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is a bump out of the speaker every once--every rotation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.63,0:21:51.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但对于最高频率 你听到的是连续的音调\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But for the highest frequency ones, you hear a continuous tone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.31,0:21:57.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是典型的脉冲星的神秘声音\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is the unearthly sound of a typical pulsar
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.56,0:22:00.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每秒旋转1.4圈\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}rotating 1.4 times each second.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.69,0:22:03.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,转换成音频 脉冲星的电波信号\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Converted to audio, the pulsar's radio signal
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.69,0:22:06.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就是催眠 重复的滴答声\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is a hypnotic, repetitious tick.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.32,0:22:12.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而调高频率 听听这颗毫秒脉冲星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But turn up the frequency and listen to this millisecond pulsar,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.53,0:22:16.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每秒旋转174圈\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}spinning 174 times per second,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.16,0:22:20.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,快得让其节拍都混在了一起 变成了刺耳的声调\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so fast that its ticks blend together to generate a ragged note
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.79,0:22:23.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那几乎就不成为音乐了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that's on the edge of turning into music.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.42,0:22:26.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那确实就是我们听到的船帆座脉冲星的声音\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's especially true when we listen to the Vela Pulsar.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.35,0:22:33.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,船帆座脉冲星有一个很棒的节奏\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Vela Pulsar has a terrific rhythm to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.81,0:22:38.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很难想象这种声音居然出自一颗转动的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's hard to imagine this sound coming from a spinning star of all things.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.35,0:22:42.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,几乎让你欲翩翩起舞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It almost makes you want to get up and dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.98,0:22:46.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,船帆座脉冲星带着宇宙节拍旋转在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Vela Pulsar is spinning with its cosmic beat
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.19,0:22:49.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个巨大的超新星遗迹的中心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at the center of a giant supernova remnant,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.11,0:22:54.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其致命的辐射横扫其周围的星际气体和尘埃\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where its killer radiation tears through the galactic gas and dust around it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.37,0:23:01.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,该超新星爆发于1.1万年前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The supernova exploded 11,000 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.21,0:23:06.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如今该脉冲星是所见X射线中最为壮观的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and today the pulsar is most spectacular when seen in X-rays.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.05,0:23:09.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每秒旋转11圈 延时照片表明\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Rotating 11 times a second, time-lapse photos show
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.88,0:23:12.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它正喷发出物质喷射\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that it's shooting out a jet of material,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.39,0:23:15.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,像失控的水龙划过太空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}whipping through space like an uncontrolled fire hose.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.94,0:23:25.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,船帆座脉冲星不同凡响的宇宙节拍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The unusual space beat of the Vela Pulsar
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.07,0:23:27.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对米奇.哈特是特殊的启发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is a special turn-on for Mickey Hart,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.65,0:23:31.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他现在正将其作为其最新作品的基础\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}who's now making it the basis for part of his latest project.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.95,0:23:39.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,啊 船帆座脉冲星非常适合作曲\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Well, Vela Pulsar, it's really made for composition,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.33,0:23:41.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为它具有有规律的节奏\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because it has a regular rhythm.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.13,0:23:48.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,音质 已经增强 感觉良好\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And sonically, it's been enhanced, and it feels good,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.80,0:23:50.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你可以把它放到曲子里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and you can use it in composition.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.63,0:23:53.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以我首先准备做船帆座\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So I went to the Vela first thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.52,0:24:02.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哈特把一些简单的脉冲星声音用在了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Hart used some simple pulsar sounds
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.81,0:24:06.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在感恩而死乐队2009年巡回演出中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}during The Dead's 2009 concert tour,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.11,0:24:08.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在他把它们开发成了古怪的乐曲\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and now he's building them into mind-bending tracks
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.53,0:24:12.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,作为其《Global Drum Project》专辑即将面世的续集\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for an upcoming sequel to his Global Drum Project album.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.78,0:24:15.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他的脉冲星声音来自外星智慧搜索中心（SETI）\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}His pulsar sounds came from the SETI Institute,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.82,0:24:19.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那里负责外星智能的搜索\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which leads the search for extraterrestrial intelligence.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.04,0:24:22.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我去过SETI\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I went to SETI,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.29,0:24:27.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们让我听到了我一直在寻求的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they led me to the sounds that I was looking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.13,0:24:31.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我以前确实没有钻研过宇宙中的声音\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I really hadn't delved into the sounds of the universe before.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.47,0:24:33.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们那里恰好有它的主脉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They just had the mother lode of it there,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.63,0:24:35.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们和我一起分享了它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they shared it with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.14,0:24:36.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,于是我将其转成了音乐\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And then I turned it into music.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.06,0:24:43.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一旦整个事情摆上了日程\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Once all of these things started to come my way,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.44,0:24:46.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我就意识到 告诉你 宇宙在歌唱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I realized that, you know, the universe was singing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.65,0:24:51.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它对我既是精神上的东西 又是娱乐\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a spiritual thing for me as well as entertainment.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.23,0:24:55.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就是说 它是乐趣 与宇宙共舞 - 乐趣无穷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I mean, it's fun, working with the cosmos--beyond fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.66,0:25:00.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是我深刻的心灵体验\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a deep spiritual experience for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.33,0:25:06.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙合唱团变得越来越大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The cosmic chorus gets much bigger
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.63,0:25:10.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当其来到叫做杜鹃47的地方时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when it comes to a place called 47 Tucanae,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.17,0:25:15.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是南方星座杜鹃座里的一个球形星团\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a globular cluster of stars in the southern constellation Toucana, the Toucan.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.05,0:25:21.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,该星团在1.6万光年之外\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The cluster is 16,000 light-years away
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.35,0:25:27.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,200万颗恒星挤在120光年直径的球形里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with 2 million stars packed into a sphere 120 light-years across.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.20,0:25:40.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不可思议的是 杜鹃47居然有22颗毫秒脉冲星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Incredibly, 47 Tucanae has 22 millisecond pulsars,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.41,0:25:45.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,个个都在离奇的星际合唱团里产生着自己的音符\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}each generating its own musical note in the bizarre stellar choir.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.00,0:25:50.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为了让毫秒脉冲星产生音符\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To get a millisecond pulsar producing a musical note,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.42,0:25:52.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你就需要让那种脉冲星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you need to start with the kind of pulsar
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.67,0:25:57.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,高速将孪生伴星里的物质吸入到自己这里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}whipped up in speed by matter spilling onto it from a binary companion star.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.22,0:26:04.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好 为了做到这一点 你必须要有很多靠近的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Well, in order to do this, you have to have lots of nearby stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.47,0:26:07.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要做到这一点还有比星团更好的地方吗？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And what better place to do that than in a star cluster?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.48,0:26:10.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此杜鹃47之类的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So something like 47 Tucanae,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.48,0:26:15.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是恒星靠近的巨大集合体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is a tremendously large collection of stars nearby,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.07,0:26:20.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是中子星变成毫秒脉冲星的理想之地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is an ideal place to have neutron stars turn into millisecond pulsars.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.70,0:26:24.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,星团里的脉冲星发出的大合唱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The collective tune from the cluster's pulsars
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.62,0:26:27.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是奇妙的太空咏叹调\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is a strangely haunting song from space,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.66,0:26:31.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由其22个风格各异的旋转所谱写\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}generated by their 22 unique and different spins.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.42,0:26:39.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,虽然整个星系里的毫秒脉冲星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}While millisecond pulsars throughout the galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.18,0:26:42.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,通常都有普通恒星作为孪生伴星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}usually have normal stars as binary companions,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.30,0:26:46.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但还是有一个双星系是一个真正的怪胎\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there is one known binary system that's a true freak,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.27,0:26:50.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为它有一颗脉冲星与另一颗脉冲星相配对\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because it has a pulsar paired with another pulsar.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.94,0:26:58.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,发现于2003年 唯一已知的双脉冲星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Discovered in 2003, the only known double pulsar
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.99,0:27:03.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,形成于一颗毫秒脉冲星同伴变成超新星之时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}formed when a millisecond pulsar's companion went supernova.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.46,0:27:10.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在这两颗脉冲星相互环绕\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And now the two pulsars orbit each other
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.87,0:27:14.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,距离非常紧凑 可以装进我们的太阳里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in a space so tight, they would fit inside our Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.97,0:27:21.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,虽然脉冲星会有伴星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}While pulsars can have companion stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.64,0:27:23.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或伴脉冲星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or companion pulsars,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.76,0:27:26.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,事情变得更加怪异了 如果我们意识到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}things get even stranger when we realize
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.31,0:27:31.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即使是经历了超新星爆发 其中有些实际上带有行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that even after a supernova explosion, some of them actually have planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.98,0:27:36.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,脉冲星没准是你期望找到行星的最后的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A pulsar is sort of the last place you'd expect to find a planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.86,0:27:40.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为产生脉冲星的恰恰是超新星爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because what happens to create a pulsar is a supernova explosion.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.66,0:27:44.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此要是普通恒星恰好有行星在其周围\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So if the original star happened to have any planets around them,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.99,0:27:48.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就有可能已经被超新星给炸飞了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they probably would have been blasted apart by the supernova.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.91,0:27:54.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而在1992年 我们太阳系外所发现的首颗行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But in 1992, the very first planets discovered outside our solar system
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.04,0:27:56.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就看到围绕着一颗脉冲星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}were found around a pulsar.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.09,0:28:01.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,波多黎各阿雷西博的巨大的射电望远镜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The giant radio telescope in Arecibo, Puerto Rico,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.55,0:28:04.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,被用来精确测量一颗脉冲星的计时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was used to precisely measure the timing of a pulsar,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.93,0:28:07.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它距离地球980光年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}980 light-years from Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.97,0:28:12.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它在不断变化 会时而快一点 时而慢一点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was changing, going a little faster and a little slower.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.06,0:28:18.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,表明了除了这颗脉冲星本身 还有什么东西存在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that implied that there was something else besides this pulsar itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.69,0:28:20.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它并不孤单\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was not isolated.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.19,0:28:23.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,原来的却有一颗行星存在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It turned out to be indeed a planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.49,0:28:27.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在的计算表明 至少有三颗行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Calculations now show there are at least three planets
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.70,0:28:32.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,围绕着该脉冲星 怀疑还有第四颗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in orbit around the pulsar, and a fourth is suspected.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.04,0:28:36.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,脉冲星的超新星可能已经摧毁了其恒星原来的行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The pulsar's supernova may have destroyed its star's original planets,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.79,0:28:40.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是新的形成了 显然是脱胎于\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but new ones formed, apparently out of debris
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.05,0:28:42.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,星系爆发所残留的碎片\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}left over from the system's explosion.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.05,0:28:48.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,脉冲星是极端力量的体现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Pulsars are the embodiment of extreme forces
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.05,0:28:50.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一旦它变成与众不同的星体后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when it comes to individual stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.39,0:28:55.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而当你将这种能量提高到整个星系后 会是啥情况呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But what happens when you ramp up such power to the level of an entire galaxy?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.73,0:28:59.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在那个级别上 我们发现了类星体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At that scale, we find the quasars.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.65,0:29:04.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是什么让它们在宇宙中鹤立鸡群的呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What makes them outshine everything else in the cosmos?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.40,0:29:08.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为何科学家会说在每一个的中心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And why do scientists say that in the heart of each one
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.62,0:29:10.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,都存在着一个怪兽呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there sits a monster?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.59,0:29:22.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,虽然脉冲星和磁星之类的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}While things like pulsars and magnetars
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.26,0:29:24.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在宇宙的奇怪星群中十分抢眼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}stand out as freakish stars in the cosmos,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.72,0:29:29.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但更为怪异的天体深藏不露\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}even stranger objects lurk much farther away
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.43,0:29:31.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那里就是类星体所呆的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where the quasars live.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.14,0:29:39.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,类星体是星系明亮耀眼的核心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A quasar is a blindingly bright core of a galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.56,0:29:42.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,巨大的黑洞在其中央\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that has a giant black hole in the center,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.28,0:29:43.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它极其明亮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it's extremely bright.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.94,0:29:46.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其亮度可以达到星系里所有恒星放在一起的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It can be as bright as 10 to 1,000 times brighter
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.91,0:29:49.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,总亮度的10到1000倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than all the stars in the galaxy put together.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.33,0:29:56.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这张哈勃望远镜照片证明了类星体可以有多亮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This Hubble Telescope photo proves just how bright a quasar can be.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.46,0:29:59.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,两个突出的天体看上去几乎一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The two prominent objects look almost the same,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.58,0:30:03.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但一个只是一颗恒星 或许就100光年以外\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but one is only a star, perhaps 100 light-years away,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.25,0:30:07.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而另一个则是类星体 在90亿光年之外\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}while the other is a quasar, 9 billion light-years away.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.43,0:30:15.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,和脉冲星一样 类星体引起天文学家最早注意\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Like pulsars, quasars were first noticed by astronomers
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.68,0:30:18.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是作为强大的电波发射源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as strong sources of radio waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.60,0:30:23.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最早的是叫做3C273的射电源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The very first was a radio source called 3C273.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.53,0:30:27.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,3C273是啥东东？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Well, what's a 3C273?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.99,0:30:32.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,剑桥射电望远镜收藏有电波的编目 -\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Cambridge Radio Telescope collected a catalog of radio--
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.66,0:30:34.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,出现在空中的明亮的射电源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}bright radio sources that were seen in the sky,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.04,0:30:37.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它是第三个剑桥编目\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it was the third Cambridge catalog,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.50,0:30:41.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其编号273是一个明亮的射电源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and its item number 273 was a bright radio source.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.71,0:30:44.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,人们设法去弄明白 这个射电源是啥玩意？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}People were trying to figure out, what is this radio source?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.21,0:30:48.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当光学望远镜指向其位置时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When optical telescopes were pointed at its position,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.26,0:30:51.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们所看到的貌似一颗恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}all they saw was what looked like a star.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.35,0:30:58.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,后来意识到这个天体非常遥远\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Then when it was realized that this object was very far away,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.73,0:31:01.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在10亿光年以外 事实上...\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}more than a billion light-years away, in fact...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.11,0:31:05.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那意味着它们实在是强大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It meant that their true power,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.19,0:31:07.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们每秒钟所释放的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the amount of energy they put out per second,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.03,0:31:10.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其功率 十分巨大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}their wattage, was enormous,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.66,0:31:12.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为看上去很亮 但又十分遥远\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because to look bright and yet be far away
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.57,0:31:15.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就是你看到的确实是一个强大的天体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}means that you've got to be really a powerful object.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.16,0:31:16.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它会是什么呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.95,0:31:22.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在 3C273被视为一个十分明亮的蓝色恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, 3C273 was identified with a rather bright, bluish star.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.92,0:31:24.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它表现为恒星模样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So it looked star-like,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.04,0:31:27.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但恒星一般不会发射电波\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but stars don't generally emit radio waves,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.21,0:31:30.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此它被称为类星射电源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so it was called a quasi-stellar radio source.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.97,0:31:36.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,类星射电源名字太长了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Quasi-stellar radio source was just too long a name,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.35,0:31:38.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以它被简称为类星体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and so it was shortened to quasar,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.64,0:31:41.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过 天哪 听上去不是很不错吧？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but, golly, doesn't that have a nice sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.94,0:31:44.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,类星体的确是个了不起的术语\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Quasar is really a great term,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.61,0:31:46.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为它意味着某种奇怪 与众不同的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because it implies something exotic and unusual,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.57,0:31:48.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,的确就是这些天体的情况\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that's really what these objects are.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.94,0:31:53.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们是巨大的黑洞 在不停地吞噬周围的物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They are huge black holes that are eating material around them
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.49,0:31:56.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,放射出大量的光 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and radiating huge amounts of light that can be seen
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.53,0:31:59.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,几乎在整个可观察到的宇宙间都能看到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}almost all the way across the observable universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.58,0:32:05.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黑洞吞噬类星体里的星系气体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The black hole consuming galactic gas inside the quasar
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.21,0:32:07.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,贪得无厌\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is so violently ravenous,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.05,0:32:10.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,天文学家给了它一个可怕的诨号\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}astronomers have given it a frightening nickname.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.93,0:32:16.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,类星体里的黑洞通常被称为怪兽\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The black holes inside quasars are often called monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.35,0:32:18.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是因为它们非常庞大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that's because they're very massive.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.77,0:32:22.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们是我们太阳质量的百万到十亿倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're a million to a billion times the mass of our Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.94,0:32:27.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们贪婪地吞噬着周围的物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they're voraciously devouring the material around them.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.11,0:32:29.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此它们的行为就好象是怪兽\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So they're sort of behaving like monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.61,0:32:35.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,类星体被认为是由星系中心的黑洞提供动力的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The quasar is said to be powered by the black hole at a galaxy's center.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.70,0:32:38.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有东西如此明亮又十分黑暗的概念\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The notion of something so bright that is also black
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.79,0:32:42.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,貌似自相矛盾的说法\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}seems like a contradiction in terms.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.12,0:32:45.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们知道黑洞是非常致密和庞大的天体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We know that black holes are objects that are so dense and massive
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.12,0:32:46.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,具有非常强的引力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and have such strong gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.58,0:32:49.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,连光都无法逃脱它们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that not even light can escape from them.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.46,0:32:50.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以那让我们怀疑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So that makes us wonder,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.63,0:32:53.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黑洞怎么可能支配所有东西呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}how can black holes power anything at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.84,0:32:57.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,答案就在于气体在落入黑洞时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the answer is that gas, as it falls into the black hole,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.55,0:33:00.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实际上会在落入之前发射出能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}can actually radiate energy before it falls in.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.14,0:33:01.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在其落入后 就消失了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}After it falls in, it's gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.68,0:33:04.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其发生的过程就是摩擦\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The way this happens is through friction.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.64,0:33:11.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要是我用双手放在一起快速搓揉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So if I take my hands and rub them together very quickly,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.23,0:33:13.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就会产生很多热量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that produces a lot of heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.70,0:33:16.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在落入黑洞的物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, the material that falls into a black hole
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.28,0:33:18.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,旋入并自我摩擦\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}spirals in and rubs against itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.49,0:33:20.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其速度极高\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it's moving at extremely high speeds.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.79,0:33:23.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因而 就类星体而言\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And so, in the case of a quasar,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.50,0:33:27.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们会看到气体相互摩擦 速度极高\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we have gas that's rubbing together and moving at very high speeds.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.92,0:33:30.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此 这样一来 它可以将自身加热到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And so, in doing so, it can heat itself up
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.04,0:33:31.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,上百万度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to even millions of degrees,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.75,0:33:34.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就能够使其发出极其明亮的光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which can cause it to glow very, very brightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.18,0:33:40.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,天文学家确信所有的星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Astronomers are confident that there are giant black holes 
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.00,0:33:42.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,中心都有巨大的黑洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the center of all galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.35,0:33:45.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那么为何所有的星系里并不同时都有类星体呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So why aren't there quasars in all galaxies, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.77,0:33:48.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为了得到类星体 你需要有两件东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To get a quasar, you need two things.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.81,0:33:52.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一 你需要有一个巨大的黑洞在星系中央\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One, you need a huge, massive black hole at the center of the galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.23,0:33:56.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是你还需要有补给的气体落入黑洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But you also need a supply of gas to fall onto that black hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.45,0:33:59.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果周围没有足够的物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If there isn't enough material around,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.20,0:34:02.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果黑洞已经基本上吃掉了周围的食物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if the black hole has basically eaten all its food around it,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.70,0:34:05.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,于是就没有什么能发光了 没有什么能发热了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}then there's nothing to shine, there's nothing to glow.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.37,0:34:07.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就不会成为明亮的类星体了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It won't be a bright quasar.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.87,0:34:10.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因而就会是 有可能是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So there could be, and probably are,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.54,0:34:13.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黑洞处在大多数星系的中央\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}black holes at the center of most galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.05,0:34:16.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但要是没有燃料补给 它们就不会成为类星体的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But if there's no fuel for them, they won't be quasars.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.18,0:34:22.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过宇宙中有条件可能使类星体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But there are conditions in the universe that may make a quasar reignite,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.51,0:34:26.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在其宿主星系中央的气体枯竭后很久之后再次点燃\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}long after the gas in its host galaxy's center gets used up.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.23,0:34:33.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,做到这一点的一个有效办法就是两个星系碰撞在一块\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And one promising way of doing this is by slamming two galaxies together.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.32,0:34:35.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们知道星系的碰撞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We know that galaxies collide.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.57,0:34:39.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在其发生时 就会产生一个宇宙大撞车\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And when that happens, it creates a big cosmic smash-up
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.95,0:34:43.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会将物质驱进星系的中心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that drives material down into the center of the galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.79,0:34:48.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,该场景有可能适用于我们自己的银河系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The scenario could apply to our own Milky Way Galaxy,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.58,0:34:51.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它正处在与仙女座的碰撞过程之中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is on a collision course with Andromeda,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.08,0:34:53.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是隔壁的巨大螺旋星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the giant spiral next door.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.05,0:34:55.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在50到60亿年里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In five or six billion years,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.55,0:34:58.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,仙女座星系会和银河系合并\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when the Andromeda Galaxy starts merging with the Milky Way Galaxy,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.93,0:35:02.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能够想象到有足够的气体被推向\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's conceivable that enough gas will be pushed
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.10,0:35:04.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,超大质量黑洞的中心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}toward the central supermassive black holes,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.68,0:35:07.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使它们变成类星体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that they'll turn into quasars.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.39,0:35:08.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在 仙女座星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, the Andromeda Galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.81,0:35:11.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可能会是两个类星体中较为明亮的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will probably be the brighter of the two quasars,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.85,0:35:15.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为仙女座里的黑洞质量远远超过\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because Andromeda has a much more massive black hole
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.11,0:35:17.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的银河系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than our Milky Way Galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.36,0:35:23.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果仙女座一旦与我们银河系合并变成类星体的话\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If Andromeda turns into a quasar when it's merging with the Milky Way Galaxy,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.12,0:35:27.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以想象它就会相当于满月的亮度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's conceivable that it'll be comparable to the full moon in brightness
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.58,0:35:30.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它就在一万光年之外\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when it's 10,000 light-years away.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.62,0:35:32.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哇\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.08,0:35:35.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即使近在一万光年之外\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even as close as 10,000 light-years away,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.96,0:35:38.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们还是看不到仙女座类星体的星盘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we wouldn't see the Andromeda quasar's disk
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.80,0:35:40.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如我们所看到的满月那样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as we can with the full moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.88,0:35:44.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,相反 它会表现为璀璨明亮的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Instead, it will appear as an intensely bright star,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.55,0:35:49.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,忽隐忽现 因为大气层的波动 宛如其他恒星那样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}flickering, due to atmospheric fluctuations, as all stars do.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.48,0:35:53.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过 难以置信的是 如果类星体形成于我们的星系中央\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But, incredibly, if a quasar forms at the center of our own galaxy,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.98,0:35:56.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们是根本看不见的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we wouldn't see it at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.19,0:35:59.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它有可能很明亮 但是有太多的尘埃\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As bright as it may be, there is so much dust
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.53,0:36:01.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在地球与星系核之间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}between the Earth and the galactic core,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.82,0:36:04.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,类星体发出的光会躲开我们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}quasar's light would be hidden from us,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.45,0:36:07.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,此时仙女座类星体则会照亮天空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}while Andromeda's would light up the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.04,0:36:11.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果我们未来出现一个局部的类星体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If there is a local quasar in our future,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.37,0:36:14.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有可能会采用任何一种形式\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it could take any number of different forms.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.33,0:36:17.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们以天体物理喷射轰击太空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They bombard space with astrophysical jets
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.21,0:36:22.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,起名字听上去像是神话生物 比如耀变体和巨龙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and sound like mythical creatures with names like blazars and DRAGNs.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.84,0:36:26.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们叙说的故事带我们穿越宇宙史诗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The stories they tell lead us through the cosmological epic
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.76,0:36:29.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们来到时间的起点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where we arrive at the beginning of time
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.39,0:36:34.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来一睹类星体是如何在宇宙诞生的那一刻帮助构建宇宙的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to find out how quasars helped build the universe at its very birth.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.41,0:36:52.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在近50年的搜索中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In nearly 50 years of searching,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.04,0:36:55.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,天文学家已经发现了近百万个类星体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}astronomers have discovered nearly a million quasars
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.33,0:36:57.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,遍布整个宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}scattered throughout the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.84,0:37:02.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,结果是 它们表现出各种各样的形式\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And as it turns out, they come in a wide variety of forms.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.72,0:37:05.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,类星体只是所谓的活跃的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A quasar is just one of a family of objects
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.38,0:37:09.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,星系核天体家族的一员 家族全都是由掉入\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}called active galactic nuclei, all of which are powered by material
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.47,0:37:12.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,星系中心巨大黑洞的物质来驱动的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}falling onto huge black holes at the center of galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.48,0:37:18.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其中超大质量黑洞吞噬\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The rate at which supermassive black holes can swallow material 
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.11,0:37:22.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,星系中央的物质的速度可以改变整个空间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the centers of galaxies can vary all over the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.90,0:37:24.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那些并不闪闪发光的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The ones that don't glow so brightly
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.78,0:37:29.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,叫做活跃的星系核 并非类星体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are called active galactic nuclei, but not quasars.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.20,0:37:34.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,活跃的星系核最离奇的特点之一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One of the most bizarre features of active galactic nuclei
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.46,0:37:39.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其中某些喷射出高速物质喷射\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are the high-speed jets of material shooting out from some of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.21,0:37:44.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,3C273 发现的首个类星体 就具有喷射\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}3C273, the first quasar to be discovered, has a jet.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.26,0:37:47.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它不仅隐约出现在可见光图像中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's only subtly apparent in the optical image,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.34,0:37:52.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而且在X光 红外线及无线电望远镜观察下尤为生动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but becomes more vivid when seen by X-ray, infrared, and radio telescopes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.52,0:37:57.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,类星体喷射是天王星上的奥秘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Quasar jets are an astronomical mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.56,0:38:00.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,多年来 科学家绞尽脑汁\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For years, scientists have racked their brains
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.11,0:38:03.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,去确切地解释它们是如何产生的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to explain exactly how they are generated.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.69,0:38:07.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如同脉冲星一样 自行车店里的飞轮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As with pulsars, a spinning wheel in a bicycle shop
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.32,0:38:10.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,解释了他们认为发挥作用的力量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}illustrates the forces they believe are at work.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.62,0:38:15.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,垂直的轮辐表示类星体磁场的磁力线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A vertical spoke represents a force line in the quasar's magnetic field.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.25,0:38:18.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,类星体的喷射或许需要两件事才能形成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The jets from quasars probably require two things to form.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.62,0:38:21.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,首先是围绕黑洞的气体盘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The first is a disk of gas that orbits the black hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.84,0:38:26.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其次是固定在气体盘上的磁力线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The second are magnetic field lines that are anchored to the disk.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.13,0:38:27.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以下就是我们对其工作的认为\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Here's how we think it works.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.84,0:38:30.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,带电粒子喜欢磁力线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Charged particles love magnetic field lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.76,0:38:32.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这样粒子会被束缚在磁力线上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So the particles get tied to the field line,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.97,0:38:36.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在其旋转时 它们就会被吹上去 远离气体盘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and as it rotates, they get blown upward, away from the disk.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.68,0:38:39.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好 最终 磁力线缠在一起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, eventually, the field line will twist around,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.81,0:38:41.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将物质压缩成一个紧紧的圆柱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}forcing the matter into a tight column,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.98,0:38:44.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也就是天文学家所谓的天体物理喷射\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or what astronomers call an astrophysical jet.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.36,0:38:49.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,喷射里的带电粒子高速运动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The charged particles in the jet are moving at high speeds
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.78,0:38:52.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能够在遥远处看到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and can be seen from great distances.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.37,0:38:55.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,几乎就像是类星体试图引人注意\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's almost as if the quasar were trying to get noticed
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.54,0:38:57.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在做一些广告\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by doing some advertising,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.71,0:39:01.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像地球上本地商贩的作为\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just as a local retailer might do on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.13,0:39:04.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种广告小玩意叫做空气舞者\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This advertising gadget is called an air dancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.05,0:39:07.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它在地球上招人注意就像类星体喷出的喷射\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It gets our attention here on Earth like the jet out of a quasar.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.13,0:39:10.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,事实上 其工作之道是一样的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And, in fact, the way it works is similar.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.02,0:39:22.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,编织布袋的行为就像类星体所产生的扭曲的磁场\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The fabric rippler acts like the twisted magnetic field generated by the quasar.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.90,0:39:25.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,里面的空气顺着布袋的内壁\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The air inside follows the walls of the rippler
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.15,0:39:28.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像带电粒子顺着类星体里的磁力线一般\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like the charged particles following the magnetic field lines in the quasar.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.53,0:39:30.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其中最大的区别\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The big difference is that here,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.65,0:39:34.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,空气的流动或许是每小时50到60英里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the air is flowing maybe 50 or 60 miles per hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.24,0:39:38.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,类星体喷射中 粒子的运动接近光速\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In a quasar jet, the particles are moving at nearly the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.25,0:39:41.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,空气舞者的表演\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The air dancer's display
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.87,0:39:45.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从其电源开始也只延展了12英尺左右\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}also extends only 12 feet or so from its power source.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.92,0:39:50.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,类星体或其它活跃的星系核喷出的喷射\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A jet coming out of a quasar
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.76,0:39:55.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不管怎样 都远远伸入太空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or another active galactic nucleus, however, stretches far into space,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.93,0:39:58.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它有可能变成一个惊人的现象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where it may turn into an amazing phenomenon
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.56,0:40:01.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,天文学家将其称之为飞龙（DRAGN）\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that astronomers call a DRAGN.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.40,0:40:07.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,DRAGN代表与活跃的星系核有关的双电波源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}DRAGN stands for double radio source associated with an active galactic nucleus.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.61,0:40:09.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是长长术语的缩写\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's sort of a long term,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.15,0:40:10.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但要是你这些东西的图像\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but if you look at pictures of these things,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.99,0:40:13.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,飞龙（DRAGN）真是恰当不过的了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}DRAGN fits much better.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.49,0:40:16.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,形成它们的是这些物质喷射\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What they are formed by is these jets of material
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.16,0:40:19.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从星系中心的黑洞喷射出来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}getting shot out from the black hole at the center of the galaxy,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.08,0:40:22.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,撞上星系之间的星际介质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}slamming into the intergalactic medium in between the galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.42,0:40:25.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,形成这些巨大的波瓣和热点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and forming these massive lobes and hot spots.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.46,0:40:27.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们可以延展到遥远\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They can extend to distances
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.46,0:40:30.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,远超过星系本身的范围\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}much larger than the size of the galaxy itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.34,0:40:34.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,飞龙的规模令人匪夷所思\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The scale of a DRAGN is mind-bending.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.26,0:40:39.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,典型者首尾之间约有150万光年 -\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The typical one is about 1.5 million light-years end to end--
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.39,0:40:43.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,远大于生成它的整个星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}far, far larger than the entire galaxy that's producing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.69,0:40:45.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果活跃的星系核\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If the active galactic nucleus
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.56,0:40:48.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,缩小到这个篮球这么大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}were scaled down to the size of this basketball,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.36,0:40:53.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那么飞龙的大小 从一个辐射波瓣到另外一个\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}then the size of a DRAGN from one radial lobe to the other
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.45,0:40:56.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,依然会是极其巨大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would still be absolutely enormous.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.16,0:40:59.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会是约整个地球的大小\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It would be about the size of the entire Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.91,0:41:08.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大多数飞龙都关联到类星体的堂兄弟 叫做射电星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Most DRAGNs are linked to quasar cousins called radio galaxies,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.46,0:41:11.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为它们是强大的电波源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}since they are strong sources of radio waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.30,0:41:13.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而同一家庭里的其他成员\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But other members of the same family
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.80,0:41:16.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是高速天体 叫做耀变体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are high-speed objects called blazars,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.01,0:41:20.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们的喷射几乎直指我们的视线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}whose jets are pointed almost directly at our line of sight,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.35,0:41:22.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使它们格外明亮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}making them incredibly bright.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.48,0:41:27.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的视线实际上把我们导向有关\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And our line of sight actually leads us to the most amazing discovery
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.86,0:41:32.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,耀变体 类星体以及射电星系最惊人的发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about blazars, quasars, and radio galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.65,0:41:37.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,谁会相信这些怪物基本上是一样的呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Who would have believed these freaks are all basically alike?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.53,0:41:40.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,通过研究这所有各类活跃的星系核\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}From studying all these types of active galactic nuclei,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.66,0:41:44.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们现在认识到 某种意义上 它们可以统统归结为同样的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we now realize that, in some sense, they can all be treated as the same thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.83,0:41:46.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只是变现为不同的形式而已\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just viewed in different ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.79,0:41:50.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尤其是 关键在于视角\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In particular, the important thing is the viewing angle,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.34,0:41:55.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即物质喷射的角度相对我们观察的角度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or the angle of the jet of material relative to the angle that we look at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.51,0:41:59.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,活跃星系的中心都非常活跃\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The centers of active galaxies are all very bright,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.18,0:42:00.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但它们有可能看上并不是那样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but they may not seem that way,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.01,0:42:03.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为其核心闪耀的物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because the shining material at their cores
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.60,0:42:06.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有可能部分或全部被隐蔽了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}can be partially or completely hidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.85,0:42:15.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们看到的这种物质包围着炸面包圈状的物质环\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This material we see is surrounded by a doughnut-shaped ring of material.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.20,0:42:21.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那物质 - 气体 尘埃 云层 - 会阻挡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That material--gas, dust, clouds-- can block the light
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.28,0:42:25.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,真正活跃的中心区域里泄漏出来的光线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from escaping from the central region that's really the active part.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.33,0:42:28.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,射电星系是其中之一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And a radio galaxy is one of those
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.37,0:42:34.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其中的炸面包圈阻挡了我们对其核心的能见度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in which the doughnut is blocking our visibility of the central core.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.55,0:42:37.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过对于类星体来说\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But in the case of a quasar,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.13,0:42:40.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们正看入炸面包圈的圆孔\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we're looking down toward the hole in the doughnut.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.89,0:42:43.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就让我们看到物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that allows us to see the material
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.51,0:42:46.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就围绕着黑洞 那就是类星体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}right around the black hole that is the quasar.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.81,0:42:50.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果这个类星体的喷射正对我们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If this quasar has its jet pointed toward us,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.31,0:42:53.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那么喷射本身就变得分外明亮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}then the jet itself becomes extremely bright.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.23,0:42:56.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就是我们称为耀变体的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is what we would call a blazar.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.74,0:43:00.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这三者都是同样的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All three are the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.53,0:43:03.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,唯一的区别就在我们的视角\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The only difference is our point of view.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.25,0:43:09.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但不管我们的视角如何\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But regardless of our viewing angle,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.54,0:43:13.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们共同具有的一个情况就是它们距离遥远\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}one thing they all have in common is their great distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.09,0:43:16.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,类星体震撼我们的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The thing that shocked us about quasars
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.01,0:43:18.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就是它们遥不可及\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was how far away they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.59,0:43:19.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们非常明亮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're so bright,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.76,0:43:21.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在那种距离上看它们如此明亮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and to see them that bright at that distance,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.43,0:43:24.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们必定是巨大无比 绝对是怪兽\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they must be titanic, absolute monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.10,0:43:26.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那么为何这些东西中没有靠近我们的呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So why are none of these things nearby us?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.89,0:43:31.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最近的类星体在20亿光年之外\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The nearest quasar is 2 billion light-years away.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.40,0:43:35.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最远的在130亿光年之外\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The most distant ones are 13 billion light-years away.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.03,0:43:40.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大多数类星体看来距离我们非常遥远\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Most quasars are seen at vast distances from us.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.70,0:43:42.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那意味着我们看到的它们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That means we're seeing them as they were
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.36,0:43:47.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是在很久很久以前 当时宇宙非常年轻\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a long, long time ago in the past when the universe was very young.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.62,0:43:51.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,类星体似乎是少年宇宙的居民\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Quasars appear to be denizens of the young universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.46,0:43:53.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,星系 在其形成的早期\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Galaxies, early in their formation,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.75,0:43:56.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,似乎已经形成了这些黑洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}seem to have produced these black holes,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.17,0:43:59.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黑洞在形成后不久就有了大量的物质吞噬\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the black holes still had a lot of material to eat
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.47,0:44:03.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此它们熠熠生辉成为了类星体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}shortly after being formed, so they glowed as quasars.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.76,0:44:09.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最早的类星体可追溯到大爆炸本身后不久\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The earliest quasars date from shortly after the Big Bang itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.48,0:44:12.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,表明它们扮演了重要的角色\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}suggesting they had an important role to play
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.19,0:44:15.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,伴随宇宙经历了早期成长的烦恼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as the universe endured its early growing pains.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.36,0:44:21.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有可能这些超大质量黑洞 就是我们所谓的类星体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's possible that these supermassive black holes that we call quasars
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.99,0:44:26.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,参与了宇宙结构的创建过程\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}were part of the process of creating structure in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.33,0:44:29.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,该过程没有完全搞明白\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The process is not completely understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.20,0:44:33.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此由于多数类星体局限在遥远的过去\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So with most of the quasars confined to the distant past,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.75,0:44:35.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们认真地研究它们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we study them intensely,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.00,0:44:39.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,希望它们能散发出宇宙起源的光辉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}hoping they'll shed greater light on the origins of the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.01,0:44:42.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,早期的巨大黑洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The early giant black holes
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.42,0:44:46.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可能是打造首批星系的引擎之一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}may have been among the engines that built the first galaxies,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.68,0:44:49.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,赋予原始气体的混沌形态\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}giving form to the chaos of primeval gas
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.52,0:44:53.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,逐步塑造出我们今天所见到的...宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that would take shape in what we now see as... the universe.
